# =============================================================================
# Webnua — environment variables.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in real values. `.env.local` is
# gitignored; this `.env.example` is the committed template. Never commit real
# keys.
# =============================================================================

# --- Supabase: client-safe (exposed to the browser) --------------------------
# The project URL and the publishable (anon) key. Both are safe to ship to the
# client — row access is enforced by RLS, not by hiding these. Use the modern
# publishable key (format: sb_publishable_...) for NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY;
# the legacy `anon` JWT also works. Wired into the browser client at
# src/lib/supabase/client.ts.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://<project-ref>.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_...

# --- Supabase: server-only (NEVER prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_) ------------------
# The service-role / secret key bypasses RLS. Used only in server contexts
# (route handlers, server actions, migration scripts). Exposing it to the
# client would defeat every RLS policy — keep it out of any NEXT_PUBLIC_ var.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# --- AI generation: Claude API (server-only) ---------------------------------
# Powers the real website generator behind the create-client flow (the
# /api/generate-site route -> src/lib/website/generate-live.ts). When unset the
# flow falls back to the deterministic generator, so the app still works
# without a key. Server-only — never prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- Public site rendering (server-only) -------------------------------------
# The host-based router (src/middleware.ts) + the published-site renderer
# (src/app/published/*). Both have sensible defaults — set these only to
# override. APP_HOST is the host that serves the Webnua app itself; every
# OTHER host is treated as a published client site. PUBLIC_SITE_DOMAIN is the
# wildcard domain client sites live under ({slug}.<domain>).
# NOTE: SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY above is REQUIRED for the renderer to read
# published content.
APP_HOST=app.webnua.com
PUBLIC_SITE_DOMAIN=webnua.dev
# Browser-readable mirror of PUBLIC_SITE_DOMAIN. Required by any 'use client'
# surface composing a preview URL (eg. the onboarding-wizard Step 7). Set this
# to the same value as PUBLIC_SITE_DOMAIN. Optional — falls back to 'webnua.dev'.
NEXT_PUBLIC_PUBLIC_SITE_DOMAIN=webnua.dev

# Absolute origin of the Webnua app, used to self-POST the internal job
# executor (enqueueJobImmediate). Optional — falls back to Vercel's runtime
# VERCEL_URL, then https://{APP_HOST}. Set it for local dev (e.g.
# http://localhost:3000) so immediate job dispatch works off-Vercel.
APP_BASE_URL=

# --- Custom domains: Vercel API (server-only) --------------------------------
# Connecting a client's custom domain (the /website hub → Connect domain)
# registers it with the Vercel project via /api/domains so Vercel issues the
# HTTPS cert. VERCEL_TOKEN is a Vercel access token; VERCEL_PROJECT_ID is this
# deployment's project id; VERCEL_TEAM_ID is only needed for team-scoped
# projects. When unset, the domain is still saved on the website row — an
# operator just adds it in the Vercel dashboard by hand. Server-only.
VERCEL_TOKEN=
VERCEL_PROJECT_ID=
VERCEL_TEAM_ID=

# --- Phase 9 custom-domain attachment ----------------------------------------
# Concierge booking URL surfaced to clients who hit a DNS-setup snag — the
# setup-in-progress UI links to it. Required for the feature; the UI hides the
# help link when unset rather than crashing. Browser-readable (NEXT_PUBLIC_).
# The server-only mirror is WEBNUA_CONCIERGE_CALENDAR_URL — set either or both;
# the browser surfaces NEXT_PUBLIC_WEBNUA_CONCIERGE_CALENDAR_URL.
NEXT_PUBLIC_WEBNUA_CONCIERGE_CALENDAR_URL=https://cal.com/your-handle
WEBNUA_CONCIERGE_CALENDAR_URL=https://cal.com/your-handle
# Batch size for the every-5-minutes domain-verification poller. Vercel's
# rate limit is around 100 req/min — a 50-row batch × 2 calls per row stays
# safely under. Tune down on a busy deployment.
DOMAIN_CHECK_BATCH_SIZE=50

# --- Internal job executor (server-only) -------------------------------------
# Shared secret guarding POST /api/internal/job-executor. The Node side reads
# it here; the pg_cron poller holds the SAME value in the database
# (private.integration_runtime_config — Postgres cannot read these env vars).
# Generate a long random value; set the env var AND run the one-time UPDATE in
# migration 0049's table comment. Server-only.
INTERNAL_JOB_SECRET=

# --- Integrations: Phase 7 ----------------------------------------------------
# Webnua owns these accounts (platform-level integrations); customers do NOT
# connect their own. Each is server-only. Slots are defined now even where
# blank — the typed env module (src/lib/env.ts) has a schema slot for each, and
# a feature degrades gracefully when its key is unset.

# Stripe — standard scope, no Connect. Bills the €299/month subscription.
# Use TEST-mode keys (sk_test_… / a test webhook secret / a test-mode Price id)
# in development; swap to LIVE-mode values for production — no code change, the
# mode is purely a function of which keys are set. STRIPE_PRICE_ID_STANDARD is
# the Price id of the €299/month recurring product created in the Stripe
# dashboard. See CLAUDE.md "Stripe billing — operator setup".
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
STRIPE_PRICE_ID_STANDARD=

# Twilio — one-way alphanumeric SMS senders (no per-customer numbers in V1).
# TWILIO_MESSAGING_SERVICE_SID is the SID of the Messaging Service the
# alphanumeric senders are registered against (required to register a sender).
# TWILIO_DEFAULT_COUNTRY (ISO-3166 alpha-2, default IE) expands national-form
# phone numbers to E.164 before sending. Use Twilio TEST credentials in dev.
# See CLAUDE.md "Twilio SMS — operator setup".
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=
TWILIO_MESSAGING_SERVICE_SID=
TWILIO_DEFAULT_COUNTRY=IE

# Resend — transactional email. EMAIL_SENDING_DOMAIN is the subdomain customer
# sub-addresses are composed against ([slug]@mail.webnua.com); it defaults to
# mail.webnua.com when unset.
RESEND_API_KEY=
RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
EMAIL_SENDING_DOMAIN=mail.webnua.com

# --- Per-tenant OAuth integrations: Phase 7 Session 2 ------------------------
# The customer owns these third-party accounts; Webnua OAuths in and stores
# per-tenant tokens (encrypted in Supabase Vault). Server-only. Google Ads is
# NOT here — operator decision: not building it.

# Google (Business Profile) — one Google Cloud OAuth 2.0 client. See the
# "Per-tenant OAuth: Google Business Profile setup" section in CLAUDE.md for
# how to create the project, enable the Google My Business API, and register
# the redirect URI. *_REDIRECT_URI_BASE is OPTIONAL — it falls back to
# {app origin}/api/integrations; set it to pin the exact URI registered with
# Google. The full callback URI is {base}/google_business_profile/callback.
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=
GOOGLE_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI_BASE=

# Meta (Ads) — placeholders. The OAuth flow is scaffolded; Meta connect is
# deferred to the Meta business session (no Meta app exists yet).
META_APP_ID=
META_APP_SECRET=
META_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI_BASE=

# HMAC key for signing the OAuth `state` token (CSRF defence on the OAuth
# round-trip). OPTIONAL — falls back to SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY when unset.
OAUTH_STATE_SECRET=

# --- RLS cross-tenant test harness (`pnpm test:rls`) -------------------------
# The harness (tests/rls/) signs in as the seeded test users and probes every
# RLS boundary. It reuses NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL + NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# above. RLS_TEST_PASSWORD is the shared test-user password (defaults to
# webnua-dev-2026 if unset). SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (above) is OPTIONAL — when
# set it enables the service-role-bypass tests and the ephemeral junior-operator
# fixture; without it those tests SKIP. See reference/rls-test-suite.md.
RLS_TEST_PASSWORD=webnua-dev-2026
